{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980953265,"sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BpkL5Ec47kmaTTpYEEvCrwyd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002191.obo","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002191.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: UBERON:0002191\n3: name: subiculum\n4: def: \"Part of the hippocampal formation that is bounded by the entorhinal cortex and area CA1. It is characterized on the CA1 border by an abrupt widening of the pyramidal cell layer. A molecular layer is present that is continuous with that of CA1, although the stratum radiatum is no longer present. The stratum oriens is also not present. adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 468).\" [BIRNLEX:1305]\n5: subset: pheno_slim\n6: subset: uberon_slim\n7: synonym: \"gyrus parahippocampalis\" RELATED [BTO:0003087]\n8: synonym: \"subicular cortex\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1305]\n9: synonym: \"subiculum cornu ammonis\" RELATED [BTO:0003087]\n10: synonym: \"subiculum hippocampi\" EXACT [FMA:74414]\n11: xref: BAMS:S\n12: xref: BAMS:SUB\n13: xref: BIRNLEX:1305\n14: xref: BM:Tel-Cx-SB\n15: xref: BTO:0003087\n16: xref: DHBA:10301\n17: xref: DHBA:10302\n18: xref: DMBA:16163\n19: xref: EMAPA:35832\n20: xref: FMA:74414\n21: xref: HBA:12896\n22: xref: MA:0000960\n23: xref: MBA:502\n24: xref: NCIT:C33648\n25: xref: neuronames:188\n26: xref: PBA:10054\n27: xref: PBA:128012354\n28: xref: SCTID:369097009\n29: xref: UMLS:C0152316 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Subiculum\"}\n30: xref: Wikipedia:Subiculum\n31: is_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\n32: relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0007613 {source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! memory\n33: relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0001953 {source=\"ABA\"} ! presubiculum\n34: relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0002728 {source=\"ABA\"} ! entorhinal cortex\n35: relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0004683 {source=\"ABA\"} ! parasubiculum\n36: relationship: part_of UBERON:0002421 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! hippocampal formation\n37: property_value: depiction \"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Hippocampus.gif\" xsd:anyURI\n38: property_value: external_ontology_notes \"In ABA SUB is part of the retrohippocampal region, along with the entorhinal area. this is in the hippocampal formation but not the hippocampal region\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"ABA\"}\n39: property_value: external_ontology_notes \"in DHBA subicular cortex is divided into subiculum, prosubiculum and supracallosal subiculum\" xsd:string\n40: property_value: function_notes \"The pyramidal neurons in the subiculum exhibit transitions between two modes of action potential output: bursting and single spiking. The transitions between these two modes is thought to be important for routing information out of the hippocampus. It is the site responsible for ictal activity in some cases of human epilepsy. It has also been implicated in working memory and drug addiction.[Wikipedia:Subiculum]\" xsd:string\n41: property_value: has_relational_adjective \"subicular\" xsd:string\n42: \n\n(End of file - total 42 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002191\nname: subiculum\ndef: \"Part of the hippocampal formation that is bounded by the entorhinal cortex and area CA1. It is characterized on the CA1 border by an abrupt widening of the pyramidal cell layer. A molecular layer is present that is continuous with that of CA1, although the stratum radiatum is no longer present. The stratum oriens is also not present. adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 468).\" [BIRNLEX:1305]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsynonym: \"gyrus parahippocampalis\" RELATED [BTO:0003087]\nsynonym: \"subicular cortex\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1305]\nsynonym: \"subiculum cornu ammonis\" RELATED [BTO:0003087]\nsynonym: \"subiculum hippocampi\" EXACT [FMA:74414]\nxref: BAMS:S\nxref: BAMS:SUB\nxref: BIRNLEX:1305\nxref: BM:Tel-Cx-SB\nxref: BTO:0003087\nxref: DHBA:10301\nxref: DHBA:10302\nxref: DMBA:16163\nxref: EMAPA:35832\nxref: FMA:74414","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/UBERON_0002191.obo","time":{"start":1778980953213,"end":1778980953249}},"id":"prt_e33871c6e00147O2FWiZ30zi9v","sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","messageID":"msg_e3387050000169zZJBJAb8MaI3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980953266,"sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xdqcGByy2YRGsH46jGL4QX4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002265.obo","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002265.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: UBERON:0002265\n3: name: olfactory tract\n4: def: \"White matter tract that contains projections from the olfactory bulb to other parts of the brain.\" [BIRNLEX:1663, http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165, ISBN:0471888893, Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract]\n5: subset: pheno_slim\n6: subset: uberon_slim\n7: synonym: \"olfactory peduncle\" RELATED [BTO:0003647]\n8: synonym: \"olfactory stalk\" RELATED [NeuroNames:283]\n9: synonym: \"pedunclulus olfactorius\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:283]\n10: synonym: \"tractus olfactorium\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:283]\n11: synonym: \"tractus olfactorius\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [BTO:0003647, Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract]\n12: xref: BAMS:olf\n13: xref: BIRNLEX:1663\n14: xref: BTO:0003647\n15: xref: DHBA:12073\n16: xref: DHBA:12074\n17: xref: EMAPA:35615\n18: xref: FMA:77626\n19: xref: HBA:9302\n20: xref: MA:0000975\n21: xref: NCIT:C33207\n22: xref: neuronames:283 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1663\"}\n23: xref: SCTID:362356008\n24: xref: UMLS:C0162435 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Olfactory_Tract\"}\n25: xref: Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract\n26: intersection_of: UBERON:0007702 ! tract of brain\n27: intersection_of: overlaps UBERON:0002264 ! olfactory bulb\n28: relationship: part_of UBERON:0011299 ! white matter of telencephalon\n29: property_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4d/Gray732.png\" xsd:anyURI\n30: property_value: external_definition \"A nervelike, white band composed primarily of nerve fibres originating from the mitral cells and tufted cells of the olfactory bulb but also containing the scattered cells of the anterior olfactory nucleus[BTO:0003647].\" xsd:string {source=\"BTO:0003647\"}\n31: property_value: external_definition \"The olfactory tract is a bundle of axons connecting the mitral and tufted cells of the olfactory bulb to several target regions in the brain, including piriform cortex, amygdala, and entorhinal cortex. It is a narrow white band, triangular on coronal section, the apex being directed upward. It lies in the olfactory sulcus on the inferior surface of the frontal lobe, and divides posteriorly into two striæ, a medial olfactory stria and a lateral olfactory stria.[Wikipedia].\" xsd:string {source=\"Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract\"}\n32: property_value: external_definition \"Tract of brain which is continuous with olfactory bulb and the cerebral cortex.[FMA]\" xsd:string {source=\"FMA\"}\n33: property_value: external_definition \"White matter tract that contains projections from the olfactory bulb to the olfactory cortex (Maryann Martone)\" xsd:string {notes=\"deprecated class\", source=\"BIRNLEX:1663\"}\n34: property_value: external_ontology_notes \"The definition was adapted from the NIFSTD class which has been retired. It has been generalized so it is applicable to various different kinds of olfactory tracts found in different taxa.\" xsd:string {editor=\"cjm\", source=\"ISBN:0471888893\"}\n35: property_value: taxon_notes \"in animals with a long snout, the olfactory tract is long, whereas it is short in short-snouted animals such as primates. In some birds the tract per se does not exist as the bulb is connected directly to the cerebral hemisphere.[ISBN:0471888893]\" xsd:string\n36: \n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002265\nname: olfactory tract\ndef: \"White matter tract that contains projections from the olfactory bulb to other parts of the brain.\" [BIRNLEX:1663, http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165, ISBN:0471888893, Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsynonym: \"olfactory peduncle\" RELATED [BTO:0003647]\nsynonym: \"olfactory stalk\" RELATED [NeuroNames:283]\nsynonym: \"pedunclulus olfactorius\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:283]\nsynonym: \"tractus olfactorium\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:283]\nsynonym: \"tractus olfactorius\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [BTO:0003647, Wikipedia:Olfactory_tract]\nxref: BAMS:olf\nxref: BIRNLEX:1663\nxref: BTO:0003647\nxref: DHBA:12073\nxref: DHBA:12074\nxref: EMAPA:35615\nxref: FMA:77626\nxref: HBA:9302\nxref: MA:0000975","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/UBERON_0002265.obo","time":{"start":1778980953221,"end":1778980953254}},"id":"prt_e33871c7f001Qu1eMcWnZ8gyK1","sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","messageID":"msg_e3387050000169zZJBJAb8MaI3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980953266,"sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pBuQV9oqO5HQwrKhGcoZD5qP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002422.obo","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002422.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: UBERON:0002422\n3: name: fourth ventricle\n4: def: \"Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large irregularly shaped cavity located on the midline of the rhombencephalon, between the medulla, pons and the isthmus ventrally and the cerebellum dorsally. It is continuous with the cerebral aqueduct anteriorally and the central canal of the spinal cord posteriorly. It communicates with the subarachnoid space through its lateral and median apertures.\" [BIRNLEX:1256]\n5: subset: pheno_slim\n6: subset: uberon_slim\n7: subset: vertebrate_core\n8: synonym: \"4th ventricle\" RELATED [MA:0000196]\n9: synonym: \"fourth ventricle proper\" RELATED [BAMS:V4]\n10: synonym: \"hindbrain ventricle\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [VHOG:0000006]\n11: synonym: \"IVth ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\n12: synonym: \"rhombencephalic ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\n13: synonym: \"rhombencephalic vesicle\" NARROW [ZFA:0000110]\n14: synonym: \"ventricle IV\" EXACT [ZFA:0000110]\n15: synonym: \"ventricle of hindbrain\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [BTO:0003426]\n16: synonym: \"ventricle of rhombencephalon\" RELATED [BTO:0003426]\n17: synonym: \"ventriculus quartus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle]\n18: xref: AAO:0011043\n19: xref: BAMS:4V\n20: xref: BAMS:V4\n21: xref: BIRNLEX:1256\n22: xref: BM:Pons-4V\n23: xref: BTO:0003426\n24: xref: CALOHA:TS-2015\n25: xref: DHBA:10669\n26: xref: DHBA:12805\n27: xref: DMBA:126651782\n28: xref: EHDAA2:0000100\n29: xref: EHDAA:896\n30: xref: EMAPA:16917\n31: xref: EV:0100310\n32: xref: FMA:78469\n33: xref: GAID:610\n34: xref: HBA:9421\n35: xref: MA:0000196\n36: xref: MBA:145\n37: xref: MESH:D020546\n38: xref: NCIT:C12828\n39: xref: neuronames:621\n40: xref: SCTID:180932000\n41: xref: TAO:0000110\n42: xref: UMLS:C0149556 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Fourth_Ventricle_of_the_Brain\"}\n43: xref: VHOG:0000006\n44: xref: Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle\n45: xref: XAO:0003099\n46: xref: ZFA:0000110\n47: intersection_of: UBERON:0004086 ! brain ventricle\n48: intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002028 ! hindbrain\n49: relationship: contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0002028 ! hindbrain\n50: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0013149 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! hindbrain vesicle\n51: property_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Gray734.png\" xsd:anyURI\n52: property_value: external_definition \"Fluid-filled brain cavity. Kimmel et al, 1995.[TAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"TAO:0000110\", ontology=\"TAO\", source=\"ZFIN:curator\"}\n53: property_value: external_definition \"Irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind. It is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space.[AAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-06-20\", external_class=\"AAO:0011043\", ontology=\"AAO\", source=\"UBERON:0002422\"}\n54: property_value: external_definition \"The fourth ventricle is an irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind. It is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space[GO][GO:0021592].\" xsd:string {source=\"GO:0021592\"}\n55: property_value: homology_notes \"The early development of most vertebrate brains is similar (...). The zebrafish neural tube follows the same basic differentiation pattern as the mammalian neural tube (reference 1); The brain develops from three embryonic enlargements of the neural tube, which later differentiate into five regions. A forebrain differentiates into telencephalon and diencephalon. The midbrain, or mesencephalon, remains undivided. The hindbrain divides into the metencephalon and myelencephalon. Cavities within the brain enlarge to form a series of interconnected ventricles (reference 2).[well established][VHOG]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-09-17\", external_class=\"VHOG:0000006\", ontology=\"VHOG\", source=\"ISBN:978-0878932504 Gilbert SF, Developmental Biology (2006) p.381-382, ISBN:978-0030223693 Liem KF, Bemis WE, Walker WF, Grande L, Functional Anatomy of the Vertebrates: An Evolutionary Perspective (2001) p.500\", source=\"http://bgee.unil.ch/\"}\n56: \n\n(End of file - total 56 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002422\nname: fourth ventricle\ndef: \"Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large irregularly shaped cavity located on the midline of the rhombencephalon, between the medulla, pons and the isthmus ventrally and the cerebellum dorsally. It is continuous with the cerebral aqueduct anteriorally and the central canal of the spinal cord posteriorly. It communicates with the subarachnoid space through its lateral and median apertures.\" [BIRNLEX:1256]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsubset: vertebrate_core\nsynonym: \"4th ventricle\" RELATED [MA:0000196]\nsynonym: \"fourth ventricle proper\" RELATED [BAMS:V4]\nsynonym: \"hindbrain ventricle\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"IVth ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"rhombencephalic ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"rhombencephalic vesicle\" NARROW [ZFA:0000110]\nsynonym: \"ventricle IV\" EXACT [ZFA:0000110]\nsynonym: \"ventricle of hindbrain\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [BTO:0003426]\nsynonym: \"ventricle of rhombencephalon\" RELATED [BTO:0003426]\nsynonym: \"ventriculus quartus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle]\nxref: AAO:0011043\nxref: BAMS:4V\nxref: BAMS:V4","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/UBERON_0002422.obo","time":{"start":1778980953228,"end":1778980953258}},"id":"prt_e33871c88001e00Q7k9JhQohzb","sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","messageID":"msg_e3387050000169zZJBJAb8MaI3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980953266,"sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lP9lTHrepAdXCLmSlJ4v3dhV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0004073.obo","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0004073.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: UBERON:0004073\n3: name: cerebellum interpositus nucleus\n4: alt_id: UBERON:0019281\n5: def: \"The nucleus composed of the globose and emoliform nuclei of the cerebellum; in some mammalian species the globose nucleus is not distinguishable.\" [MP:0009984]\n6: subset: pheno_slim\n7: synonym: \"interposed nucleus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\n8: synonym: \"interposed nucleus of cerebellum\" EXACT []\n9: synonym: \"interposed nucleus of the cerebellum\" EXACT [NeuroNames:1243]\n10: synonym: \"interposed nucleus of the cerebellum\" RELATED [NLXANAT:20081242]\n11: synonym: \"interpositus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\n12: synonym: \"interpositus nucleus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\n13: xref: DHBA:12399\n14: xref: DHBA:12613\n15: xref: DMBA:16929\n16: xref: EMAPA:37819 {source=\"MA:th\"}\n17: xref: HBA:9578\n18: xref: neuronames:1243\n19: xref: NLXANAT:20081242\n20: xref: Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus\n21: is_a: UBERON:0000125 ! neural nucleus\n22: relationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:32524 {source=\"ISBN:0471888893\"} ! Amniota\n23: relationship: never_in_taxon NCBITaxon:8570 {source=\"ISBN:0471888893\"} ! Serpentes\n24: relationship: part_of UBERON:0002130 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! cerebellar nuclear complex\n25: property_value: external_definition \"The interposed nucleus is a deep nucleus of the cerebellum and is composed of the globose nuclei and the emboliform nuclei. It is located in in the roof (dorsal aspect) of the fourth ventricle, lateral to the fastigial nucleus. It receives its afferent supply from the anterior lobe of the cerebellum and sends output via the superior cerebellar peduncle to the red nucleus.\" xsd:string {source=\"Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus\"}\n26: property_value: function_notes \"modulates muscle stretch reflexes of proximal limb muscles[WP]\" xsd:string\n27: \n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: UBERON:0004073\nname: cerebellum interpositus nucleus\nalt_id: UBERON:0019281\ndef: \"The nucleus composed of the globose and emoliform nuclei of the cerebellum; in some mammalian species the globose nucleus is not distinguishable.\" [MP:0009984]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"interposed nucleus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\nsynonym: \"interposed nucleus of cerebellum\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"interposed nucleus of the cerebellum\" EXACT [NeuroNames:1243]\nsynonym: \"interposed nucleus of the cerebellum\" RELATED [NLXANAT:20081242]\nsynonym: \"interpositus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\nsynonym: \"interpositus nucleus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus]\nxref: DHBA:12399\nxref: DHBA:12613\nxref: DMBA:16929\nxref: EMAPA:37819 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: HBA:9578\nxref: neuronames:1243\nxref: NLXANAT:20081242\nxref: Wikipedia:Interposed_nucleus","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/UBERON_0004073.obo","time":{"start":1778980953236,"end":1778980953263}},"id":"prt_e33871c8f001tpJMf3wFckSeAj","sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","messageID":"msg_e3387050000169zZJBJAb8MaI3"}}
