{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981042766,"sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_9JqJnrvn2GXsaPENv4TUOgkC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Validate DHBA identifiers","prompt":"You are validating ontology cross-reference identifiers in the local UBERON checkout. Confirm whether the following DHBA mappings are the ones requested for removal in issue #3627 and whether the remaining DHBA xrefs on the same terms appear contextually plausible based on local ontology context and any available issue text only. Target removals: DHBA:12399 from UBERON:0004073 cerebellum interpositus nucleus; DHBA:10669 from UBERON:0002422 fourth ventricle; DHBA:12074 from UBERON:0002265 olfactory tract; DHBA:12471 from UBERON:0002047 pontine raphe nucleus; DHBA:10301 from UBERON:0002191 subiculum. Do not edit files. Return a concise validation summary and any concerns.","subagent_type":"general","task_id":"","command":"identifier validation for issue #3627"},"output":"task_id: ses_1cc786c7effeocGISGhLoRgjpo (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nValidation summary:\n\n- Issue `#3627` explicitly requests removal of exactly these five mappings:\n  - `DHBA:12399` from `UBERON:0004073` cerebellum interpositus nucleus\n  - `DHBA:10669` from `UBERON:0002422` fourth ventricle\n  - `DHBA:12074` from `UBERON:0002265` olfactory tract\n  - `DHBA:12471` from `UBERON:0002047` pontine raphe nucleus\n  - `DHBA:10301` from `UBERON:0002191` subiculum\n\n- In the current local `uberon-edit.obo`, none of those five target DHBA xrefs are present on those terms.\n- The same five terms currently carry these DHBA xrefs instead:\n  - `UBERON:0004073` -> `DHBA:12613`\n  - `UBERON:0002422` -> `DHBA:12805`\n  - `UBERON:0002265` -> `DHBA:12073`\n  - `UBERON:0002047` -> `DHBA:12475`\n  - `UBERON:0002191` -> `DHBA:10302`\n\nContextual plausibility of remaining DHBA xrefs:\n\n- All five retained DHBA xrefs are on neuroanatomical human-brain terms, which is broadly consistent with DHBA usage in local ontology context.\n- The retained xrefs also sit alongside other brain-atlas style mappings (`HBA`, `MBA`, `BAMS`, `neuronames`, etc.), which makes them locally plausible.\n- `UBERON:0002191` is especially plausible because the term has a local note: `in DHBA subicular cortex is divided into subiculum, prosubiculum and supracallosal subiculum`, which supports a DHBA mapping on `subiculum`.\n- `UBERON:0002265` and `UBERON:0002191` changed by only `1` from the removal targets (`12074` -> `12073`, `10301` -> `10302`), which is consistent with an off-by-one or nearby-term correction rather than complete removal of DHBA coverage.\n- For the other three, the retained IDs are different but still not obviously suspicious from local context alone.\n\nConcerns:\n\n- The local checkout appears already consistent with the requested removals, so if this validation is meant to check pending edits, there may be nothing left to remove in this branch.\n- I cannot confirm DHBA identifier semantics beyond local ontology context and issue text alone, so the retained DHBA xrefs should be treated as contextually plausible, not definitively verified against DHBA source data.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","sessionId":"ses_1cc786c7effeocGISGhLoRgjpo","model":{"modelID":"gpt-5.4","providerID":"codexoauth"},"truncated":false},"title":"Validate DHBA identifiers","time":{"start":1778980983708,"end":1778981042759}},"id":"prt_e33878589001OIgZ407W3Z7UiV","sessionID":"ses_1cc79a0daffezrqJA5azHfs3zs","messageID":"msg_e3387806d001ykfEz9P5UsFJzg"}}
